[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":653},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F17\u002Feslint-switch-style-standard-to-airbnb\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F17\u002Feslint-switch-style-standard-to-airbnb\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F17\u002Feslint-switch-style-standard-to-airbnb\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F17\u002Feslint-switch-style-standard-to-airbnb\u002F":628,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2022\u002F02\u002F17\u002Feslint-switch-style-standard-to-airbnb\u002F":637},"\u002Fjavascript\u002F20220217\u002F3940015361\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":610,"date":611,"description":612,"extension":613,"lang":614,"meta":615,"navigation":616,"path":617,"readingMinutes":618,"seo":619,"standalone":620,"stem":621,"tags":622,"tldr":625,"updated":611,"url":626,"__hash__":627},"content\u002Fen\u002FJavaScript\u002Feslint-switch-style-standard-to-airbnb.md","How to Switch ESLint Style (Standard → Airbnb) Without Losing Your Mind","1001520451",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":605},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,33,41,48,55,60,71,100,103,114,119,129,135,147,162,165,169,183,189,195,201,445,457,500,519,524,535,571,583,591,601],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"When you build a project, you'll almost always reach for a style manager to keep everyone's code consistent. On the frontend, that tool is ESLint. The problem is, once you've locked in a style at the start, switching to a different one later turns out to be kind of annoying. So this post is about how to move ESLint from the Standard style over to Airbnb.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"a-plain-project","A plain project",[17,25,26,27,32],{},"I won't cover how to add ESLint to a project here — if you're not familiar with that, check out ",[28,29,31],"a",{"href":30},"\u002Fjavascript\u002F20210218\u002F4003233584\u002F","this post"," (article in Mandarin).",[17,34,35,36,40],{},"When you run ",[37,38,39],"code",{},"eslint --init"," you'll get a few choices to make. I'll pick Standard here.",[17,42,43],{},[44,45],"img",{"alt":46,"src":47},"eslint init","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FN8rgYAI.png",[17,49,50,51,54],{},"Once it finishes installing, ESLint creates a config file for you called ",[37,52,53],{},".eslintrc.js",".",[17,56,57],{},[44,58],{"alt":53,"src":59},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FYyh2RfP.png",[17,61,62,63,66,67,70],{},"What else? Open ",[37,64,65],{},"package.json"," and you'll notice a few packages got added to ",[37,68,69],{},"devDependencies",":",[72,73,74,80,85,90,95],"ul",{},[75,76,77],"li",{},[37,78,79],{},"eslint",[75,81,82],{},[37,83,84],{},"eslint-config-standard",[75,86,87],{},[37,88,89],{},"eslint-plugin-import",[75,91,92],{},[37,93,94],{},"eslint-plugin-node",[75,96,97],{},[37,98,99],{},"eslint-plugin-promise",[17,101,102],{},"(You might end up with different packages depending on what you chose.)",[17,104,105,106,108,109,111,112,54],{},"So now, say we want to switch from Standard to Airbnb — how do we do that? Basically you delete ",[37,107,53],{}," along with every ",[37,110,79],{},"-related package in ",[37,113,69],{},[17,115,116],{},[44,117],{"alt":69,"src":118},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FFqoiUVc.png",[17,120,121,122,125,126,128],{},"You also need to delete the ",[37,123,124],{},"node_modules"," folder, then run ",[37,127,39],{}," again and pick the ESLint style you want. In my case I went back through it and switched from Standard to Airbnb.",[17,130,131],{},[44,132],{"alt":133,"src":134},"Airbnb","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F9ayAOy4.png",[17,136,137,138,140,141,143,144,146],{},"We won't bother looking at ",[37,139,53],{},", but take a look at what changed in ",[37,142,65],{},"'s ",[37,145,69],{},". It basically swaps over to installing these packages instead:",[72,148,149,153,158],{},[75,150,151],{},[37,152,79],{},[75,154,155],{},[37,156,157],{},"eslint-config-airbnb-base",[75,159,160],{},[37,161,89],{},[17,163,164],{},"So you can see the two styles pull in totally different dependencies.",[12,166,168],{"id":167},"vue-cli","Vue Cli",[17,170,171,172,174,175,178,179,182],{},"In a Vue Cli or Vite environment, we usually don't use ",[37,173,39],{}," to set up ESLint. Instead we go through another route — ",[37,176,177],{},"vue add eslint",". You can read more about that in ",[28,180,31],{"href":181},"\u002Fvue\u002F20200522\u002F1986801509\u002F"," (article in Mandarin); I won't repeat the reasoning here.",[17,184,185,186,188],{},"First, same as before, let's spin up a Vue environment. I'll use Cli as the example and run ",[37,187,177],{},", picking the Standard style.",[17,190,191],{},[44,192],{"alt":193,"src":194},"Standard","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FaY0mxiI.png",[17,196,197,198,200],{},"Then let's take a look at the base ",[37,199,65],{}," first:",[202,203,208],"pre",{"className":204,"code":205,"language":206,"meta":207,"style":207},"language-json shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","{\n  \"name\": \"cli\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"private\": true,\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"serve\": \"vue-cli-service serve\",\n    \"build\": \"vue-cli-service build\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"core-js\": \"^3.6.5\",\n    \"vue\": \"^3.0.0\",\n    \"vue-router\": \"^4.0.0-0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@vue\u002Fcli-plugin-babel\": \"~4.5.0\",\n    \"@vue\u002Fcli-plugin-router\": \"~4.5.0\",\n    \"@vue\u002Fcli-service\": \"~4.5.0\",\n    \"@vue\u002Fcompiler-sfc\": \"^3.0.0\",\n    \"sass\": \"^1.26.5\",\n    \"sass-loader\": \"^8.0.2\"\n  }\n}\n","json","",[37,209,210,219,236,249,263,272,285,296,302,310,323,336,347,352,360,373,385,397,409,422,433,439],{"__ignoreMap":207},[211,212,215],"span",{"class":213,"line":214},"line",1,[211,216,218],{"class":217},"sMAXC","{\n",[211,220,222,226,229,233],{"class":213,"line":221},2,[211,223,225],{"class":224},"sKpQp","  \"name\"",[211,227,2